      "@danielmewes There's a `sysinfo()` function described here: http://linux.about.com/library/cmd/blcmdl2_sysinfo.htm.\r\n\r\nIt seems to work fine on `newton` with\r\n```cpp\r\n#include <iostream>\r\n#include <sys/sysinfo.h>\r\n\r\nint main() {\r\n    struct sysinfo info;\r\n    if (sysinfo(&info) == 0) {\r\n        std::cout << info.totalram << std::endl;\r\n    } else {\r\n        std::cout << \"error\" << std::endl;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nbut you should probably test it on a machine with swap to see what it returns there."
